# Research comparisons need axes

When writing research/comparison docs (e.g. “X vs Prisma Next”), avoid placing two statements near each other without explaining the relationship.

Every comparison section must make the shared axis explicit, using at least one of:

- **Knob**: what the user actually does/chooses (import, config, API call)
- **Invariant**: what the system can guarantee because of that choice
- **Trade-off**: what you gain and what you give up
- **So what**: the concrete implications for portability, safety, performance, testing, policy, or roadmap

If a comparison cannot be expressed on a shared axis, treat it as an **open question** or restructure the section (don’t force an apples-to-oranges juxtaposition).

